From d4099dfa75b837def31227ccb5f3fc08e7ea36f8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 01:39:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(design-system): unified alignment + popup application
 form

One system, every page:
- Single .kicker class replaces three ad-hoc kicker styles (same color,
  size, weight, tracking on light and dark)
- Every section/page header now uses the identical left-aligned
  section-header treatment with the 3px accent rule: homepage (all
  sections incl. dark ones via --dark variant), pricing, solutions,
  resources, dashboard, legal pages
- Removed decorative hero hairline (no customer value)
- ROI disclaimer and solutions CTA aligned to the system (were centered)

Popup form (as requested):
- New ApplyCTA button + accessible modal: backdrop blur, Escape and
  backdrop-click close, body scroll lock, dvh-capped height with
  internal scroll on small phones, entrance animation, reduced-motion
  safe
- Hero primary CTA opens the popup directly; #talk-to-expert section
  retains the button so all existing deep links still convert
- Merged the redundant back-to-back Final CTA + Contact sections into
  one dark conversion section (less scroll, same function)
